      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so, if they take that route, how should they address the common counter-argument that strict enforcement is essentially just inhumane or xenophobic? they need a way to pivot the debate back to these principled arguments about sovereignty and the rule of law so the round doesn't just become an emotional argument about individual cases.",
